    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>That is not possible, but you can add an anonymous initializer like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>final int anInt = ...;\nObject a = new Class1()\n{\n  {\n    System.out.println(anInt);\n  }\n\n  void someNewMethod() {\n  }\n};\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Don't forget final on declarations of local variables or parameters used by the anonymous class, as i did it for anInt.</p>\n"
  }, {
