  "title" : "Accessing constructor of an anonymous class",
  "body" : "<p>Lets say I have a concrete class Class1 and I am creating an anonymous class out of it.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Object a = new Class1(){\n        void someNewMethod(){\n        }\n      };\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Now is there any way I could overload the constructor of this anonymous class. Like shown below</p>\n\n<pre><code>Object a = new Class1(){\n        void someNewMethod(){\n        }\n        public XXXXXXXX(int a){\n          super();\n          System.out.println(a);\n        }\n      };\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>With something at xxxxxxxx to name the constructor?</p>\n"
}